┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ STEP 1: Load Dataset (Road Network)                         │
│                                                             │
│  Input:  USA-road-d.NY.gr (distance graph)                  │
│          USA-road-t.NY.gr (time graph)                      │
│          USA-road-d.NY.co (coordinates)                     │
│                                                             │
│  Output: NetworkX graph with 264K nodes, 730K edges         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                            ↓
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ STEP 2: Generate Test Queries (Routing Questions)          │
│                                                             │
│  Process:                                                   │
│  1. Pick random node pairs from graph                      │
│  2. Calculate geographic distance between them             │
│  3. Classify into buckets:                                 │
│     • Short (0-5 km): 50 queries                          │
│     • Medium (5-50 km): 50 queries                        │
│     • Long (>50 km): 50 queries                           │
│                                                             │
│  Output: queries.csv (150 source→target pairs)            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                            ↓
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ STEP 3: Run Benchmark (Test Algorithm Performance)         │
│                                                             │
│  For each objective (distance, time):                      │
│    For each query (150 queries):                           │
│      1. Start timer & memory tracker                       │
│      2. Run Dijkstra(source, target)                       │
│      3. Record:                                            │
│         • Runtime (seconds)                                │
│         • Peak memory (MB)                                 │
│         • Nodes expanded (count)                           │
│         • Path cost (total weight)                         │
│      4. Stop timer & memory tracker                        │
│                                                             │
│  Output: dijkstra_results.csv (300 rows: 150×2 objectives)│
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                            ↓
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ STEP 4: Visualize & Analyze Results                        │
│                                                             │
│  Create charts showing:                                     │
│  • How performance scales with query distance              │
│  • Comparison between distance vs time objectives          │
│  • Distribution of metrics across queries                  │
│  • Relationship between time, memory, and efficiency       │
│                                                             │
│  Output: dijkstra_performance.png (6 charts)              │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
